<TEXTAREA NAME="Text" COLS="60" ROWS="6" WRAP="VIRTUAL">Blue - (gasp....gasp)...where can I go!?

(Blue navvigates a group of corners, hearing screams behind him, until he sees an elevator shaft. He runs over to it, and then realises he never bothered to notice a metal cage over it. He looks around, the stairs are old and creaking, and he isn't sure if he can make it down without falling through. The wook looks extremely weak and it covered in dust. He looks around, the screams are becoming even louder. He uses the tool as a lockpick as fast as he can, but he isn't sure where to use it. He starts making a hole in the cage just far enough in to press the call button, hoping the cage would go past too. The gunshots now bounce of the walls around him)

Blue - Come on...COME ON!!!

(Blue ends up pounding the cage. He can't even feel his hands after 5 hits. But, somehow, it works. The cage opens, and a gunshot flies off the space Blue's head was in, followed by more screams. Blue jumps inside dropping the tool, and hits the button for the Ground Floor. It wont open. He stares at it, the doors wont even close. Suddenly, he sees a red light flashing above him)

Blue - ...!?...WHAT!?

Light - &quot;ELEVATOR SERVICE IS UNAVAILABLE&quot;

Blue - NOOOO!!!!

(Up ahead, even more bullets fly astray. He can see Reptile coming around the corner now)

Blue - NOOOOO!!!!

(Reptile turns away for a brief second to blast away another two guards. He turns towards Blue, who stares at him, almost paralysed. Suddenly it hits him, the stairs! He runs outside, barely dodging two bullets, and dashes down the stairs as fast as he can, every one creaking beneath him, and nearly breaking)</TEXTAREA></TD>

